 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Associate Director, IO Discovery/Translation BioXcel Therapeutics Morristown, NJ Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Design preclinical in vivo studies including efficacy, translational, mechanism of action, safety/toxicology studies. Supervise work of CROs for successful completion of outsourced in vitro and in vivo projects in the area of Immuno-oncology. Re-innovate/repurpose existing molecules for the treatment of cancer patients Closely collaborate with other IO team members on different aspects of Immuno-oncology projects. Evaluate existing biology/preclinical data of therapeutic leads. Evaluate external opportunities for licensing in oncology. Closely work with cross-functional teams from Artificial Intelligence, clinical development, Business Development and other groups. Authoring manuscripts for publication in high impact factor scientific journals 
 Requirements/Qualifications 
Requires a PhD in Life Sciences/Cell Biology/Biochemistry with a minimum of 10+ years of experience 
In-depth knowledge of cancer in vivo models and pharmacokinetic studies 
Should have experience in designing animal studies for Immuno-oncology 
Strong background in cancer biology and associated signalling pathways, especially those that are relevant to Immuno-oncology. 
Pre-clinical drug discovery experience advancing both small molecules and biologics candidates through early research stages into development pipeline is preferred. 
Biotech experience is preferred. 
Excellent verbal and written communication skills are required. 
Strong interpersonal, organizational and planning skills 
Team player mentality is required for accomplishing Company goals 
